{
  "texts": [
    "in a donut figure can be deformed (without breaking) to follow either of the loops a or b an integer number of times.",
    "The fact that there are exactly two one-dimensional loops from which all others can be constructed indicates that the number of one-dimensional holes of the donut is one.",
    "Hence, the 1-homology counts the number of these holes.",
    "A 2-dimensional hole is a void, for example, the void within a hollow sphere, torus, or Swiss cheese in 3 dimensions.",
    "The k-dimensional holes are counted specifically by the Betti numbers."
  ]
}